Package gov.nasa.jpl.ammos.mpsa.aerie.merlinsdk

Interface MerlinAdaptation<Event>

  • All Known Implementing Classes:
    AbstractMerlinAdaptation
    @Deprecated
public interface MerlinAdaptation<Event>
    Deprecated.
    A mission-agnostic interface to the capabilities provided by a mission-specific adaptation.

    The Merlin system, and Aerie in a broader sense, must be able to extract information from an adaptation in order to tune its multi-mission capabilities to the needs of a specific mission. This interface is the top-level entry point: the first adaptation object that Merlin will interact with is an MerlinAdaptation.

    An implementation of MerlinAdaptation must be registered in a file in the adaptation JAR named META-INF/services/gov.nasa.jpl.ammos.mpsa.aerie.merlinsdk.MerlinAdaptation. This file shall contain the fully-qualified name of the implementing class, such as gov.nasa.jpl.ammos.mpsa.aerie.banananation.Banananation.

    An implementation of MerlinAdaptation must provide a no-arguments constructor. This constructor should not generally perform any work, as the adaptation object may be constructed simply to check metadata or perform other validation.

    An implementation of MerlinAdaptation must be annotated with @Adaptation.

    See Also:
